---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'
import Header from '../components/Header.astro'
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro'
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy — Extol">
  <Header />

  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-600 text-bark-900 mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-warm-gray-400 mb-1"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> March 13, 2026</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-warm-gray-400 mb-12"><strong>Last Updated:</strong> March 16, 2026</p>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2 id="introduction">1. Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        Extol, Inc. ("Extol," "we," "us") operates the Extol platform, including
        the Brij community event tool and associated services (collectively, the
        "Services"). This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, store,
        share, and protect your personal information.
      </p>
      <p>
        We are committed to transparency. We do not sell your personal
        information. We collect only what we need to provide the Services. You
        can delete your account and data at any time.
      </p>

      <h2 id="information-we-collect">2. Information We Collect</h2>

      <h3>2.1 Information You Provide</h3>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Data Type</th>
            <th>When Collected</th>
            <th>Purpose</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Account information</strong></td>
            <td>Registration</td>
            <td>Name, email address, password hash — to create and secure your account</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Profile information</strong></td>
            <td>Optional</td>
            <td>Display name, bio, community affiliations — to identify you within communities</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Event data</strong></td>
            <td>Event creation (coordinators)</td>
            <td>Event name, description, date, location — to organize community activities</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Contribution records</strong></td>
            <td>Activity tracking</td>
            <td>Description of contributions, timestamps — to record your community participation</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Payment information</strong></td>
            <td>Paid subscriptions</td>
            <td>Processed by our payment processor; Extol does not store credit card numbers</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>2.2 Information Created Through Use</h3>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Data Type</th>
            <th>When Created</th>
            <th>Purpose</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Attendance records</strong></td>
            <td>Check-in at events</td>
            <td>Records that you attended a community event — created by you or by a coordinator on your behalf</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Peer attestations</strong></td>
            <td>Community interaction</td>
            <td>Records where community members attest to your participation or contributions</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Governance activity</strong></td>
            <td>Governance participation</td>
            <td>Votes, proposals, staking actions — to operate community governance</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Wallet address</strong></td>
            <td>Extol governance activation</td>
            <td>A blockchain wallet address generated for on-chain attestations</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>2.3 Information Collected Automatically</h3>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Data Type</th>
            <th>Purpose</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Device and browser information</strong></td>
            <td>User-Agent, IP address, device type — for security, fraud prevention, and service optimization</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Usage data</strong></td>
            <td>Pages viewed, features used, session duration — to improve the Services</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Log data</strong></td>
            <td>Server logs for debugging and security monitoring — retained for 90 days</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>2.4 Information Created by Coordinators</h3>
      <p>
        Community coordinators may record attendance or activities on your
        behalf. When this happens:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>You are notified the first time a coordinator creates a record for you</li>
        <li>You can review all records created on your behalf</li>
        <li>You can delete any or all of these records at any time</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="data-use">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>We use your information to:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Provide the Services</strong> — account management, event coordination,
          attendance tracking, governance tools</li>
        <li><strong>Process on-chain attestations</strong> — translate your activity into
          pseudonymous blockchain records (only if your community uses Extol
          governance features)</li>
        <li><strong>Communicate with you</strong> — service announcements, notifications about
          records created on your behalf, responses to your inquiries</li>
        <li><strong>Improve the Services</strong> — usage analytics, bug fixes, feature
          development</li>
        <li><strong>Ensure security</strong> — fraud detection, abuse prevention, account
          protection</li>
        <li><strong>Comply with legal obligations</strong> — tax reporting, law enforcement
          requests, regulatory requirements</li>
      </ol>
      <p>We do <strong>not</strong> use your information to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Sell to third parties</li>
        <li>Target advertising</li>
        <li>Build profiles for sale to data brokers</li>
        <li>Train AI models on your personal data without your explicit consent.
          If your Collective votes to participate in community-initiated
          research, you retain an individual right to opt out regardless of
          the Collective's vote. Consent for AI training use is always
          individual and opt-in — a Collective vote authorizes the Collective's
          participation, not yours personally</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="identity-to-wallet-link">4. The Identity-to-Wallet Link</h2>
      <p>This section describes the most sensitive data we hold.</p>

      <h3>4.1 What It Is</h3>
      <p>
        If your community uses Extol governance features, we create and maintain
        a link between your account identity (name, email) and your blockchain
        wallet address. This link exists in Extol's secure infrastructure
        between Brij and the public blockchain.
      </p>

      <h3>4.2 Why It Exists</h3>
      <p>The link is necessary to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Connect your community activity (recorded in Brij) to your on-chain
          attestations</li>
        <li>Display your governance token balance and voting weight in the app</li>
        <li>Enable you to participate in governance through a familiar interface
          rather than directly interacting with blockchain tools</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>4.3 Who Can Access It</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>You</strong> — you can see your own wallet address and linked records</li>
        <li><strong>Extol operations staff</strong> — limited access for support and
          debugging, subject to internal access controls and audit logging</li>
        <li><strong>No one else</strong> — we do not share the link with communities,
          coordinators, other users, or third parties except as required by law
          (see Section 6)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>4.4 How We Protect It</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>The link is stored in encrypted form in our database</li>
        <li>Access is restricted to authorized personnel with logged access</li>
        <li>The link is the first data deleted when you delete your account</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>4.5 What Happens When You Delete</h3>
      <p>
        When you delete your account, the identity-to-wallet link is
        permanently destroyed. Your wallet address becomes an anonymous orphan
        on the blockchain — the on-chain records persist but are no longer
        linked to any identity in our systems. There is no backup copy and no
        way to re-link. See Section 8 for full deletion details.
      </p>

      <h2 id="on-chain-data">5. On-Chain Data</h2>

      <h3>5.1 What Goes On-Chain</h3>
      <p>
        If your community uses Extol governance features, the following data
        may be recorded on a public blockchain:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Hashed attestation records (a one-way cryptographic hash of your
          activity data — not the raw data itself; see Section 5.4 for details
          on irreversibility)</li>
        <li>Community governance token positions (your participation commitment
          and portable balances, recorded as token data — not as dollar amounts)</li>
        <li>Governance votes and proposals</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Community tokens are recorded as on-chain positions. Some positions
        are permanent commitments that cannot be reversed. Portable balances
        may change over time due to earning, spending, or depreciation.
        Community tokens have no public market price or exchange rate to any
        currency.
      </p>

      <h3>5.2 What Does NOT Go On-Chain</h3>
      <p>The following data is <strong>never</strong> written to the blockchain:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your name, email, or other personally identifying information</li>
        <li>Raw event data, attendance records, or contribution details</li>
        <li>The identity-to-wallet link</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>5.3 Permanence</h3>
      <p>
        On-chain data is public and permanent. It cannot be modified, deleted,
        or made private after recording. However, on-chain records use
        pseudonymous wallet addresses — without the identity-to-wallet link
        (which you can delete), they are not linked to a person.
      </p>

      <h3>5.4 Hashing</h3>
      <p>
        Attestation data recorded on-chain is a one-way cryptographic hash. The
        hash cannot be reversed to reveal the underlying data. Once the
        off-chain source record is deleted, the hash is a meaningless string
        with no reversibility path.
      </p>

      <h2 id="sharing">6. When We Share Your Information</h2>
      <p>We share personal information only in these circumstances:</p>

      <h3>6.1 With Your Community</h3>
      <p>
        Your community coordinators and members can see information you make
        available through your community participation — your display name,
        contributions, attendance, and governance activity. This is the purpose
        of the Services.
      </p>

      <h3>6.2 Service Providers</h3>
      <p>We use third-party service providers for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Cloud hosting and infrastructure</li>
        <li>Payment processing</li>
        <li>Email delivery</li>
        <li>Analytics (aggregated, not individual)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Service providers are contractually bound to use your information only
        to provide services to Extol and are prohibited from using it for their
        own purposes.
      </p>

      <h3>6.3 Legal Requirements</h3>
      <p>
        We may disclose personal information if required by law, subpoena,
        court order, or government request. When legally permitted, we will
        notify you before disclosure.
      </p>

      <h3>6.4 Business Transfers</h3>
      <p>
        In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your
        information may be transferred as part of the transaction. We will
        notify you before your information becomes subject to a different
        privacy policy.
      </p>

      <h3>6.5 Attestation API — Third-Party Verification</h3>
      <p>
        The Extol platform provides an Attestation API that allows authorized
        third parties to verify your community participation credentials.
      </p>
      <p><strong>How it works:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>A third party (e.g., a potential employer, platform, or licensing
          partner) requests verification of your community participation
          credentials</li>
        <li>You receive a consent request specifying: who is asking, what data
          they want to verify, and why</li>
        <li>You explicitly approve or deny each verification request</li>
        <li>If approved, the third party receives only the specific credential
          data you authorized — not your full profile, activity history, or
          wallet address</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>What is shared:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Community membership status (active/inactive)</li>
        <li>Participation credentials (e.g., "verified contributor in
          [Collective] for [duration]")</li>
        <li>Governance participation level (if you consent)</li>
        <li>Attestation scores or tiers (if you consent)</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>What is never shared through the API:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your identity-to-wallet link</li>
        <li>Raw activity records or attendance history</li>
        <li>Other community memberships you have not authorized for disclosure</li>
        <li>Governance vote content (how you voted — only that you participated)</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Consent model:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Verification requires your explicit, per-request consent</li>
        <li>You can revoke access to previously shared credentials at any time</li>
        <li>A Collective's governance vote does not authorize sharing your
          individual credentials — individual consent is always required</li>
        <li>You can disable API access entirely in Settings</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>6.6 With Your Consent</h3>
      <p>
        We may share information for purposes not listed here with your
        explicit, informed consent.
      </p>

      <h2 id="your-rights">7. Your Rights</h2>

      <h3>7.1 Access</h3>
      <p>
        You can access all personal information we hold about you through your
        account settings. This includes attendance records, contribution
        records, peer attestations, and (if applicable) your wallet address.
      </p>

      <h3>7.2 Correction</h3>
      <p>You can correct your account information at any time through Settings.</p>

      <h3>7.3 Deletion</h3>
      <p>
        You can delete your account and all associated data at any time. See
        Section 8.
      </p>

      <h3>7.4 Data Portability</h3>
      <p>
        You can export your data in a standard, machine-readable format (JSON)
        through Settings. This includes your activity history, contributions,
        and attestation records.
      </p>

      <h3>7.5 Opt-Out of On-Chain Features</h3>
      <p>
        If your community activates Extol governance features, you can opt out
        of on-chain attestations while remaining a community member using Brij
        features.
      </p>

      <h3>7.6 California Residents (CCPA/CPRA)</h3>
      <p>
        If you are a California resident, you have additional rights under the
        California Consumer Privacy Act, as amended by the California Privacy
        Rights Act:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Right to know</strong> what personal information we collect, use, and share</li>
        <li><strong>Right to delete</strong> your personal information</li>
        <li><strong>Right to opt out</strong> of the sale of personal information (we do not
          sell personal information)</li>
        <li><strong>Right to non-discrimination</strong> for exercising your privacy rights</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise these rights, contact <a href="mailto:privacy@extol.work">privacy@extol.work</a> or use the
        self-service options in Settings.
      </p>

      <h3>7.7 EU/EEA Residents (GDPR)</h3>
      <p>
        If you are located in the European Union or European Economic Area, you
        have additional rights under the General Data Protection Regulation:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Legal basis:</strong> We process your data based on (a) your consent,
          (b) performance of our contract with you (these Terms), (c) our
          legitimate interests in operating the Services, or (d) compliance
          with legal obligations</li>
        <li><strong>Right to restrict processing</strong> — you can ask us to limit how we
          use your data</li>
        <li><strong>Right to object</strong> — you can object to processing based on
          legitimate interests</li>
        <li><strong>Right to lodge a complaint</strong> with your local data protection
          authority</li>
        <li><strong>Data transfers</strong> — we transfer data from the EU/EEA to the United
          States. We use Standard Contractual Clauses to protect your data
          during transfer.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="deletion">8. Data Deletion</h2>

      <h3>8.1 How Deletion Works</h3>
      <p>
        When you delete your account, a single action triggers deletion across
        all layers:
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Your activity data:</strong> Complete deletion of your user record, all
        attendance records, all contribution records, and all peer attestations.
        This is a clean, irreversible wipe.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Your identity link:</strong> Permanent deletion of the connection between
        your identity and your blockchain wallet address. Your wallet address
        becomes anonymous — it exists on the blockchain but is connected to no
        one in our systems.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>On-chain records:</strong> Attestations, token balances, and staking positions
        on the public blockchain cannot be deleted. However, without the
        identity link, these records are pseudonymous data that cannot be linked
        back to you.
      </p>

      <h3>8.2 What We Cannot Delete</h3>
      <p>
        We cannot delete data recorded on a public blockchain. We can — and do —
        delete the only link between that data and your identity.
      </p>

      <h3>8.3 Backup and Log Purge</h3>
      <p>When you delete your account, we also:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Remove your data from backups within 30 days</li>
        <li>Purge any log entries containing your identity link within 30 days</li>
        <li>Retain only anonymized, aggregated data that cannot identify you</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>8.4 Coordinator-Created Records</h3>
      <p>
        Records that a coordinator created on your behalf are deleted when you
        delete your account. The coordinator is not notified of individual
        record deletions.
      </p>

      <h2 id="data-security">9. Data Security</h2>

      <h3>9.1 Measures</h3>
      <p>We implement industry-standard security measures including:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Encryption in transit (TLS) and at rest (AES-256)</li>
        <li>Access controls and authentication for all internal systems</li>
        <li>Regular security assessments</li>
        <li>Audit logging for access to sensitive data (especially the
          identity-to-wallet link)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>9.2 Breach Notification</h3>
      <p>
        In the event of a data breach affecting your personal information, we
        will notify you within 72 hours of becoming aware of the breach, as
        required by applicable law. Notification will include the nature of the
        breach, the data affected, and steps we are taking in response.
      </p>

      <h2 id="data-retention">10. Data Retention</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Data Type</th>
            <th>Retention Period</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Account information</td>
            <td>Until you delete your account</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Activity records (Brij)</td>
            <td>Until you delete your account</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Identity-to-wallet link</td>
            <td>Until you delete your account</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>On-chain data</td>
            <td>Permanent (blockchain)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Server logs</td>
            <td>90 days</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Backup copies</td>
            <td>Purged within 30 days of account deletion</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Payment records</td>
            <td>As required by tax law (typically 7 years)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Aggregated analytics</td>
            <td>Indefinite (anonymized, non-personal)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Pre-community activity data</td>
            <td>See Section 10.1 below</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>10.1 Pre-Community Activity Data</h3>
      <p>
        Brij allows coordinators to create events and track participation
        before a formal community or Collective is formed. This early-stage
        data — attendance records, contributions, and peer attestations
        collected through Brij before any community governance structure
        exists — is subject to the following rules:
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>If a community forms:</strong> Pre-community data becomes part of the
        community's activity history, subject to all standard retention and
        deletion policies.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>If a community never forms:</strong> Pre-community activity data is retained
        for 12 months from the last recorded activity. After 12 months of
        inactivity with no community formation, we will:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Notify the coordinator and all participants with recorded activity</li>
        <li>Provide a 30-day window to export data</li>
        <li>Delete all pre-community activity data, including attendance records
          and contribution records</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <strong>Your rights during this period:</strong> Even before a community forms,
        you retain full rights to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>View all records associated with your account</li>
        <li>Delete your own records at any time</li>
        <li>Export your data</li>
        <li>Delete your account entirely</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="childrens-privacy">11. Children's Privacy (COPPA)</h2>

      <h3>11.1 General Policy</h3>
      <p>
        The Services are not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly
        collect personal information from children under 13 without verifiable
        parental consent.
      </p>

      <h3>11.2 Youth-Serving Communities</h3>
      <p>Communities that serve participants under 13 must comply with COPPA by:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Obtaining verifiable parental consent before any data collection</li>
        <li>Providing parents with notice of what data is collected and how it
          is used</li>
        <li>Allowing parents to review, delete, or refuse further collection of
          their child's data</li>
        <li>Not conditioning participation on the child providing more data than
          necessary</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>11.3 Parental Rights</h3>
      <p>Parents of children under 13 can:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Review all data collected about their child</li>
        <li>Request deletion of their child's data</li>
        <li>Refuse further data collection</li>
        <li>Contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@extol.work">privacy@extol.work</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="cookies-and-tracking">12. Cookies and Tracking</h2>

      <h3>12.1 Essential Cookies</h3>
      <p>We use essential cookies for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Session management (keeping you logged in)</li>
        <li>Security (CSRF protection)</li>
        <li>Preferences (language, display settings)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        These cookies are necessary for the Services to function and cannot be
        disabled.
      </p>

      <h3>12.2 Analytics</h3>
      <p>
        We use privacy-respecting analytics to understand how the Services are
        used. We do not use third-party advertising trackers. Analytics data is
        aggregated and cannot identify individual users.
      </p>

      <h3>12.3 No Third-Party Advertising</h3>
      <p>
        We do not serve third-party advertisements. We do not share data with
        advertising networks. We do not track users across other websites.
      </p>

      <h2 id="international-data-transfers">13. International Data Transfers</h2>
      <p>
        Extol is based in the United States. If you access the Services from
        outside the US, your data is transferred to and processed in the US.
      </p>
      <p>
        For EU/EEA users, we use Standard Contractual Clauses approved by the
        European Commission to ensure adequate protection of your data during
        transfer.
      </p>

      <h2 id="changes">14. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Material changes
        will be communicated with at least 30 days' advance notice through the
        platform or by email. The "Last Updated" date at the top reflects the
        most recent revision.
      </p>

      <h2 id="contact">15. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>For privacy questions, data requests, or concerns:</p>
      <p>
        <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacy@extol.work">privacy@extol.work</a>
      </p>
      <p>
        For GDPR-related inquiries, you may also contact your local data
        protection authority.
      </p>

      <p class="text-sm"><em>Copyright 2026 Extol, Inc. All rights reserved.</em></p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
  .prose h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-bark-900, #2C1810);
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .prose h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-bark-900, #2C1810);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .prose p, .prose li, .prose td {
    color: var(--color-warm-gray-500, #6B5E54);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .prose ul, .prose ol {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    list-style-type: disc;
  }
  .prose ol {
    list-style-type: decimal;
  }
  .prose li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .prose a {
    color: var(--color-terracotta-500, #C75B3F);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  .prose table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .prose th {
    text-align: left;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-bark-900, #2C1810);
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem 0.5rem 0;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-warm-gray-200, #E5DDD5);
